==English==

===Etymology===
Late Latin ''crenellare'', kernellare: See French ''créneler'' to indent. See [[Crenelle]].

===Alternative spellings===
*[[crenelate]] (''US'')

===Transitive verb===
'''crenellate''' ('''[[crenellating]]''', '''[[crenellated]]''', '''[[crenellated]]''')
# To furnish with crenelles.
# To indent; to notch.
#:''crenellated leaf''

